“Camper updates” sent by camp director throughout the week
End of camp week celebration with achievement awards and recognition

Full Day Camps (ages 9-16) provide an excellent opportunity for junior golfers to learn or improve their technical skills as well as develop strong course management skills. Participants are segmented into smaller groups based on their experience level in order to create the most favorable learning environment possible.
Half Day Camps (ages 7-13) are designed to create in the “new junior golfer” up through those playing at an intermediate level. Participants are segmented into smaller groups based on their experience level in order to create the most favorable learning environment possible. For three hours each day, campers learn or hone their skills with a strong emphasis placed on golf’s fundamentals and well as fun!


The Instructors
To be the best, you must learn from the best. That’s why every junior golf camp instructor has been trained and tested in all aspects of the game by the PGA of America.  Our promise–is to support, encourage, and respect each and every one of our campers and authentically inspire them to reach their full potential, both on and off the golf course.







Brian Bickford - Camp Director
Brian Bickford is in his tenth year as Head Golf Professional and Director of Golf at Val Halla. Brian is passionate about teaching junior golfers and is himself a product of Val Halla’s junior golf programs in his youth. Brian was PGA Professional of the Year in 2013 and recipient of the President’s Award for Player Development in Maine in 2013, 2014 and 2015.
 



